main event: The report describes an observation of a bright light in the sky by the crew of the USCGC Matagorda on November 29, 1964.
interesting points: The light was observed at coordinates 33.54N 166.02E.
The light was at a high position angle of 45 degrees and moving on a course of 188 degrees true.
No other details about the object, such as size, shape, or maneuvers, are provided.
The report was distributed to various military and intelligence agencies, including the Department of the Air Force, the Central Intelligence Agency, and the Defense Intelligence Agency.
The conclusion of the report is that the object was likely the satellite Echo I, which was in the appropriate position at the reported time of observation.
